<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>chanuitl spiking issue </title>
<style>
    body {
        background-color: #000000;
        color: #66ff99;
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 40px;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }
    h1, h2 {
        color: #7CFFB2;
    }
    .box {
        border: 1px solid #2ecc71;
        padding: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
    }
</style>
</head>
<body>



<div class="box">
<h2>Current Situation</h2>
<ul>
<li>EU868 LongFast shared RF environment</li>
<li>Channel utilization spikes from ~20% to 50–60% during text traffic</li>
<li>Multiple nodes experiencing same behaviour</li>
<li>Overlapping external mesh (Silent Legion) present in RF range</li>
<li>MQTT gateways present on multiple networks</li>
<li>Belived to be feed back loop it might not be so please keep that in mind</li>
<li>We have to do damage control our selfs</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="box">
<h2>Likely Causes</h2>
<ul>
<li>High mesh density causing retransmission amplification</li>
<li>RF overlap between multiple regional meshes: We have links to the north and south via rf </li>
<li>MQTT bridging increasing message propagation paths</li>
<li>With SL making heavy use of MQTT its highly likely that some nodes will end up with two paths to them either rf or mqtt this is 
what is possibly causing the high chanuitl on many nodes </li>
<li> Too many client nodes in one location MAKE use of client mute more </li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="box">
<h2>Immediate Actions</h2>
<ul>
<li>Enable MQTT ignore consistently across all nodes unfortunately this is to try and minimise our traffic hitting SL MQTT</li>
<li>set nodes to local_only: this should stop important nodes trying to decode private channels they dont have the key for it also helps
with battery life</li>
<li>Keep telemetry and position intervals conservative 12hrs pings for fixed nodes 3hr pings for mobile and making use of smart postioning</li>
<li>Monitor packet types during spikes (routing vs text) :this is currently being done</li>
<li>Identify worst-affected nodes in the hopes of pin pointing the sole cause if there is one </li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="box">
<h2>Network Strategy</h2>
<ul>
<li>Limit MQTT gateways to controlled bridge nodes only: those running the mhuk UPLINK only mqtt are fine as it is UPLINK only for maps and data
its things like using the meshtastic default MQTT or http://meshtastic.sytes.net/ MQTT (same one SL is using) that need to be controlled sorry</li>
<li>Avoid uncontrolled RF↔MQTT↔RF bridging loops</li>
<li>make use of client mute more</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="box">
<h2>Expected Outcome</h2>
<ul>
<li>Reduced airtime spikes during messaging</li>
<li>Lower RF contention on hilltop nodes</li>
<li>More predictable channel utilisation</li>
<li>Improved stability under load</li>
<li>WE ALL NEED TO SHARE THE SAME CHANNEL/FREQUENCY MAKING USE OF UNCONTROLLED MQTT IS NOT HELPFUL IN A ALREADY LARGE MESH</li>
</ul>
</div>

</body>
</html>
